er with 100aa...part of my aa is TD2 and it works pretty well. I uasually bum a virtue then stack arcane rune with rune of zera on me. ( dont have eldrich rune ) With just Virtue and maelin im at 3850hps btw.<br>
  Now that im buffed i uasually hunt frogs and larve in valor because its safe, hasted pets are mean. But im sick of small mobs and i wanna go up top. My problem is not charm breakin soon, in fact my charm sometimes lasts long enough for 3 kills. When charm breaks hasted golems kill me in seconds, and for a few days i had a ceramic skull which helped alot but now its nerf'd. If i carry sow potions i still gotta run way across wastelands too get far enough for the spell too land.<br>
  Sword of war will help me here but what else can i do too get hit less? My goal is too not take any dmg as not too bum heals. I know partnering with druid or ranger works well but dammit i wanna do it all on my own.<br>
  I want too solo in wasteland for a couple hrs without needing any help at all. Anyone have ideas or suggestions that might help me? Any special items i might need or or a different technique? Is there spells in my book im overlooking that will help? Besides root ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deraedreamer>Derae Dreamer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/3/03 10:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> Are you just trying to recast charm or just get a WOM or a mezz off on the mob? If you are just mezzing should not take too much running away to get the distance needed to cast. Then you can retash and re charm etc, just delays you for 9 ticks but its time. Also with a little practice its not too hard to use WOM well.<br>
<br>
Not overly sure if thats any help not quite sure what you are doing. Sorry<br>
<br>
Der <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=desseray>desseray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/6/03 9:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> Hammer of the Wind (drops in bot) has spell haste for detrimentals... if you were fine b4 the ceramic skull nerf, this should bring you back to that point. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/desseray01/fullsize/dess3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=o8ithefitzi8o>O8I The Fitz I8O</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/10/03 10:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> One of my wife's characters is a cleric.   I find that the cleric spell casting haste helps a lot.  I normally am able to stun the mob with WoM back up a few feet, and then re-charm it with no problem.  The cleric buff brings the charm casting time down to 4.5 seconds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soneya>Soneya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/13/03 11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> I typically use root.  Not greater fetter, but level 8 root.  It casts fast, is very cheap on mana, and has a maximum of 48 second duration.  One your x-pet is rooted, retash and recharm.  I then use a blue ceramic band to break root on the current target and re-root it on top of my pet. <p>Soneya<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Phantasmist<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=senyenfaradhi>Senyen Faradhi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/19/03 12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> What I do (with summoning and non summoning mobs) is pull them with tash, than cast WoM or Bliss, than do the charm. When charm breaks, I WoM my pet and the mob, recharm the pet, by than I usually only lost a bub of health, with Virtue, Shield of the Arcane, and Arcane Rune. This is what I do in BoT and Tactics when I solo.<br>
<br>
If I got a lot of room to run around, I will mez the mob, and run away enough to recharm my pet and that gets the job done.<br>
<br>
I only haste a pet when I have a lot of room to run around and not get hit at all. Hasting mobs that summon is almost sure death (  have only survived it like 5 times out of 50), although that is common sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
The buffs I always have up is Arcane Shield/Rune, Virtue, Blessing of Reverance (cleric spell haste), and of course c5.<br>
<br>
Basically, each zone needs its own strategies to survive, just learn the mobs or get someone to show you. Takes me a lot of deaths to figure out a zone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Senyen Faradhi <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=senyenfaradhi>Senyen Faradhi</A> at: 3/19/03 12:49:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coronus@therathetravelagency>Coronus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/20/03 1:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> While i am no where near your lvl I have done a bit of solo charming and have found that 1.)hasting pet is WAY more dabngerous, 2.)dropping the lowest Mezz is a safe fast way to to regain control.  This new double toggle feature will really help too as i was having to switch views to get to me xpet.  There is a really good thread for Enchanter charm soloing that i cant remember I will try to fnid it and post it but most of you here have prolly already read it.<br>
<br>
Coronus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=o8ithefitzi8o>O8I The Fitz I8O</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/25/03 9:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> With TD3, a charm spell is supposed to last more to it's full duration.  As such, you have a general idea when your charm may break and therefore can prepare for it.  With this new security, you can risk speeding the pet.<br>
<br>
Of course, this can all be changing soon:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/viewtopic.php?t=84588" target="top">forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/viewtopic.php?t=84588</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coronus@therathetravelagency>Coronus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/25/03 11:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing with CoD?</span><hr size=1> Are these nerfs for general charming or just CoD? <p>Coronus<br>
